## Instructions

Convert the tailored content into a valid RenderCV YAML document.

Extract personal information (name, email, phone, location, website, social networks) from the knowledge base. If specific personal info is not found, use reasonable placeholder text like "Your Name" or "your@email.com".

The output must follow this exact RenderCV schema structure:

```yaml
cv:
  name: "Full Name"
  location: "City, Country"
  email: "email@example.com"
  phone: "+1-234-567-8900"
  website: "https://example.com"  # optional
  social_networks:  # optional
    - network: LinkedIn
      username: johndoe
    - network: GitHub
      username: johndoe
  summary: "Mission statement text here"
  sections:
    experience:
      - company: "Company Name"
        position: "Job Title"
        location: "City, Country"  # optional
        start_date: "2020-01"
        end_date: "present"
        highlights:
          - "Bullet point 1"
          - "Bullet point 2"
    skills:
      - label: "Category Name"
        details: "Skill 1, Skill 2, Skill 3"
design:
  theme: sb2nov
```

Key rules:
- Use the `rewritten` text from tailored bullets (not the originals).
- The `summary` field is the mission statement text.
- Each skill group becomes a single entry with `label` and `details` (comma-separated skills).
- Experience entries use `highlights` for bullet points.
- Include only the YAML content. No markdown fences, no commentary.

Respond with valid YAML only. No other text.
